Qing Period Dresses - 清代后宫服

We have visited China once or twice in our grand journey of fashion discovery around the ages and continents, however one or two trips to China are not enough to fully enjoy all the culture.

Spanning for thousands of years, China has graced the world with many refined clothing and designs who still are paid homage to this day.

Today, in LoRA format, I would ask you to enjoy and pay homage to this grand culture through the dresses worn by the Chinese emperor's courtesans in the Qing period (1644 - 1911).

Download this LoRA and travel through time and space!
